mn_text]  <div class=\"video-popup\" id=\"popup3\" style=\"background-image: url('https:\/\/www.atwtravels.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/places-to-visit-in-maldives.jpg');\">\n    <div class=\"play-button \"><i class=\"fa fa-play\"><\/i><\/div>\n    <div class=\"video-popup-box\">\n      <div class=\"close-button fa fa-times\"><\/div>\n      <div class=\"video-wrapper\">\n        <iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/qv9y4T1jFI4\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n      <\/div>\n    <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n\n  <script>\n    (function() {\n      var popup = document.getElementById(\"popup3\");\n      var playButton = popup.querySelector(\".play-button\");\n      var closeButton = popup.querySelector(\".close-button\");\n      var videoPopupBox = popup.querySelector(\".video-popup-box\");\n      var videoPopupWrapper = popup.querySelector(\".video-wrapper\");\n\n      playButton.addEventListener(\"click\", function() {\n        videoPopupBox.style.display = \"block\";\n        videoPopupWrapper.style.width = \"50%\";\n      });\n\n      closeButton.addEventListener(\"click\", function() {\n        videoPopupBox.style.display = \"none\";\n        var iframe = popup.querySelector(\"iframe\");\n        iframe.src = iframe.src;\n        videoPopupWrapper.style.width = \"50%\";\n      });\n\n      \/\/ Reload iframe when the video popup is closed\n      videoPopupBox.addEventListener(\"transitionend\", function(event) {\n        console.log(\"enters\");\n        if (event.propertyName === \"display\" && videoPopupBox.style.display === \"none\") {\n            console.log(\"success\");\n          var iframe = popup.querySelector(\"iframe\");\n          iframe.src = iframe.src;\n\t\t  videoPopupWrapper.style.width = \"50%\";\n        }\n      });\n    })();\n  <\/script>\n  [\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner disable_element=&#8221;yes&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1702387219647{margin-top: 30px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column_inner][vc_btn title=&#8221;Read Less&#8221; align=&#8221;center&#8221; el_class=&#8221;readlessBTN&#8221;][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;All You Need to Know About Bali Tour&#8221; use_theme_fonts=&#8221;yes&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A visit to Bali is a must if you&#8217;re looking to make memories last a lifetime. Few places in the world are as iconic as this beautiful island. Beautiful beaches, lush greenery, and vibrant culture make this place a paradise destination. At ATW Travels, we help plan personalized <em><strong>Bali tour packages<\/strong><\/em> to suit your budget and travel style.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Why Visit Bali?&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">While Indonesia is an archipelago of over 13,600 islands, Bali is perhaps the most exotic and popular. It has been attracting travelers even since the days of Marco Polo, who visited the place in the 13th century. Indians have been visiting the island for trade since the 7th century. There are plenty of reasons to choose Bali tour packages \u2013 we have listed a few for you.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Idyllic Beaches&#8221; font_container=&#8221;tag:h3|text_align:left&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bali is famous for its unending and world-famous beaches, and one of the most obvious reasons people visit this tropical island. Every beach here has its natural charm and unique character \u2013 from the soft white sand and extreme water sports to limestone cliffs. Some popular beaches include Kuta, Legian, Jimbaran, and Seminyak. Each of these beaches has its specialty. If Kuta is famous for its streetside food stalls and surfing, Legian is known for its beach clubs, while Nusa Dua is famous for its luxury resorts and remote beaches.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Unique Culture&#8221; font_container=&#8221;tag:h3|text_align:left&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bali&#8217;s beauty goes beyond its captivating beaches and forest landscapes. Culture is at the core of their daily lives for the Balinese, followed by religion. They love to dance, music, and art but are equally passionate about cockfighting. The Balinese belief system revolves around Tri Hita Karana, i.e., the three causes of goodness. Balinese life is based on maintaining harmony between God, people, and nature. No wonder, even with all the commercial elements, you&#8217;ll be amazed by the genuine intensity with which they celebrate Nyepi or the Day of Silence. Gamelan, a typical Balinese orchestra, is equally unique thanks to its various percussion instruments. If you&#8217;re looking for Bali tour packages around the New Year, don&#8217;t miss the Suwat or Water Festival.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Balinese Religion&#8221; font_container=&#8221;tag:h3|text_align:left&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bali is a predominantly Hindu province, but Balinese Hinduism is very different from the Indian variety, with a lot of emphasis on Maya, illusion, and karma. There are over 20,000 temples in and around Bali, and a specific function or celebration for every Balinese calendar day of 250 days. Balinese temples are classified into different categories: Pura (temple) Tirtha being water temples, Pura Segara being sea temples, Pura Kahyangan being directional temples, etc. Some of Bali&#8217;s best and most famous temples include the Lempuyang Temple, Tanah Lot temple, Ulun Danu Beratan temple, Goa Gajan, Besakih temple, and Sarawati temple. At ATW Travels, our all-inclusive Bali tour packages include some must-visit temples.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;World Class Accommodation&#8221; font_container=&#8221;tag:h3|text_align:left&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are plenty of accommodation options, from luxury resorts in the middle of paddy fields to beach resorts and affordable hostels. Each of these places offers value for money \u2013 ranging from infinity pools that open up to paddy fields to exclusive access to water-based activities. With <a href=\"https:\/\/www.atwtravels.com\/\">ATW Travels<\/a>&#8216; Bali tour packages, you get to stay at clean, well-equipped, and enjoyable places. We have something for everyone &#8211; from private villas to hotel rooms in international chain hotels and midrange hotels.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Culinary Paradise&#8221; font_container=&#8221;tag:h3|text_align:left&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">While there are plenty of food options to suit an international palate ranging from French and Italian to Mexican, Chinese, and Indian, authentic Balinese cuisine is in a league of its own. Traditional Balinese food is rich in flavor and spices and is exceptionally fragrant. Galangal, shallots, white pepper, chili peppers, palm sugar, and fish paste are the basic ingredients in any Balinese food. You could either sample some of their authentic dishes as one of the many warungs or sign up for Balinese cooking classes when booking our Bali tour packages for couples.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Bali is A Perfect Destination for Everyone&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">ATW Travels offers myriad packages based on your travel style and activities. We are committed to providing a dream vacation to everyone, promising a flawless experience from start to end. Choose from our range of Bali tour packages that suit your needs best:<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Bali Tour Packages for Family&#8221; font_container=&#8221;tag:h3|text_align:left&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bali is an excellent destination for family vacations. From beautiful beaches and plenty of water sports activities to jungle safaris, there are plenty of things to do and enjoy for people of all ages. The Waterbom Bali and Elephant Safari Park are excellent for kids, while teenagers and adults can enjoy surfing, diving, snorkeling, and other water sports. Bali is equally famous for its massages and ancient healing therapies.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Bali Tour Packages for Couples&#8221; font_container=&#8221;tag:h3|text_align:left&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bali is one of the most romantic destinations in the world. Ranging from wild water rafting and surfing to swimming, there are plenty of couple activities for you to enjoy. You could sign up for a couple&#8217;s culinary class or visit textile-making classes. Art lovers can visit factories engaging in woodcarving, stone carving, and manufacturing musical instruments. Bali has the perfect climate all year through, with temperatures ranging between 25\u00baC to 30\u00baC. Even if it gets hot, you can always head to the mountains to cool off in one of the many mountain retreats. For some sightseeing, hop on a motorbike to explore the Balinese countryside or trek in the rice fields while a guide explains rice&#8217;s life cycle and admires Bali&#8217;s agrarian traditions. For fun, you could try climbing a coconut tree or join the locals as they prepare authentic dishes. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.atwtravels.com\/contact-us\/\">Contact us<\/a> for more information about our range of Bali tour packages for couples.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Bali Luxury Packages&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bali is the perfect luxury destination for people seeking an exclusive and out-of-this-world holiday experience. You could stay at one of the many high-end water villas and dine at world-class restaurants. From private yacht and helicopter rides to private island tours, we promise an experience of a lifetime.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Places to Visit in Bali&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With its beautiful landscapes and captivating beaches, visitors to Bali are spoilt for choice. You could visit some of the most serene temples or explore hidden waterfalls while visiting some of Bali&#8217;s best and most visited places. Some of the famous places included in our Bali tour packages include:<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Ubud&#8221; font_container=&#8221;tag:h3|text_align:left&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ubud is a serene paradise and a haven for relaxation and healing, with lush green ride paddies, dense forests, and ornate temples. The place offers plenty of accommodation options, ranging from luxury resorts to family villas. You could sign up for a relaxing massage, enjoy the Ubud Food Festival, or go snorkeling. Some famous attractions in Ubud include the Campuhan Ridge Walk, the Tukad Cepung Waterfalls, Empul Temple, the Ubud Art Market, and Karangasem.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Nusa Dua&#8221; font_container=&#8221;tag:h3|text_align:left&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Nusa Dua is famous for its luxury resorts with plenty of activities, including beaches, temples, museums, and cultural parks. Some famous beaches in Nusa Dua include Pantai Mengiat, Pantai Geger, Pantai Samuh, Sawangan Beach, and Pandawa Beach. You could go shopping to buy souvenirs and other handicrafts or stroll along the Nusa Dua promenade. Sea walking is equally popular for people who don&#8217;t know swimming.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Kuta&#8221; font_container=&#8221;tag:h3|text_align:left&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Kuta is one of the most popular destinations in Bali. Millions of tourists visit the place every year to enjoy its beaches and nightlife. You can surf at Kuta Beach or enjoy a romantic dinner at Jimbaran Beach. Paragliding is equally popular at Pandawa Beach. The Uluwatu Temple in South Kuta is famous for its beautiful sculptures. Children can have fun at the Waterbom water park, while shopping addicts can splurge at the Beachwalk Shopping Centre. <a href=\"tel:+919693339999\">Call<\/a> our travel experts to learn more about our Bali tour packages for a detailed travel itinerary of all the places you can visit.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;The Best Time to Visit Bali&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As earlier said, Bali is pleasant all year round. But some months are better and worth booking Bali tour packages, depending on your budget and travel plans. For instance, April to October is the perfect time for family vacations. People who look forward to bright and sunny days and enjoy some of its water sports activities can visit during this season. But November to March is the winter season and less crowded \u2013 hence ideal to book Bali tour packages for couples.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Looking for information about exclusive Bali tour packages? Call our tour operators to plan a personalized vacation to the world&#8217;s best holiday destination!<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;View All Bali Packages&#8221; use_theme_fonts=&#8221;yes&#8221; el_id=&#8221;gt_all_packages&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1702534524213{margin-top: 20px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;}&#8221; el_class=&#8221;float-left mob-m0 gt-all-packages&#8221;][vc_column][vc_column_text][\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row&#8221; el_class=&#8221;float-left cta-package&#8221; el_id=&#8221;cta_section_tour&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1683730393587{background-image: url(https:\/\/www.atwtravels.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/tour-package-cta-yellow-background.png?id=29418) !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/4&#8243;][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;Share Your Ideal Tour: Let Us Customize!&#8221; use_theme_fonts=&#8221;yes&#8221; el_class=&#8221;cta_tour_heading&#8221;][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/4&#8243; el_class=&#8221;display-inline-div-layer&#8221;][vc_btn title=&#8221;Enquire Now&#8221; align=&#8221;right&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1683269208464{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}&#8221; el_class=&#8221;enqu_btnmr-10&#8243; el_id=&#8221;ctaenqury&#8221;][vc_btn title=&#8221;+91 9693339999&#8243; align=&#8221;right&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1683183917329{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}&#8221; link=&#8221;url:tel%3A%2B919693339999&#8243;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row disable_element=&#8221;yes&#8221;][vc_column]<div class=\"st-faq-new st-faq\">\r\n    <h4>FAQs:<\/h4>\r\n                                <div class=\"item active\">\r\n                    <div class=\"header\">\r\n                        <i class=\"input-icon field-icon fa\